sions prior to 24, JVM arguments allowed the security manager, but that's not the case anymore. I could potentially call nullSafeLoadClass directly using ServiceLoaderUtilInvoker, but it’s tricky since there's no direct public API. Tests already use the invoker for safeLoadClass and newInstance, so need to adjust methods to handle nullSafeLoadClass, while ensuring no metadata edits will cause issues.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_x7ZcoyD9iTcWKC36TY85KU6L|fc_039c11950725165e016a246be5468081968186d8ab85053998", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jakarta.xml.bind/jakarta.xml.bind-api/4.1.0-M1/src/test/java/jakarta/xml/bind/ServiceLoaderUtilInvoker.java", "limit": 220}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 18305, "output": 459, "cacheRead": 11776, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30540, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780771801559, "responseId": "resp_039c11950725165e016a246bdaa4e481968b65c99a9ebdbf35"}}
