[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing security tests**\n\nI need to fix tests that are throwing a SecurityException from Permission.checkGuard in Java 24. The existing code only installs the security manager if it's supported. But it seems that Permission.checkGuard might not be supported, and I need to find a way to access nullSafeLoadClass. I could call it via an invoker in the same package to avoid checkPackageAccess. The developer mentioned no reflection is allowed, so I have to stick to the normal public API. However, that path fails due to library issues on JDK.\n\n**Examining Java security changes**\n\nI need to understand if checkGuard is unsupported in Java 24 when there's no security manager. The existing fallsBack test only uses the SecurityManager if it's supported. Under Java versions prior to 24, JVM arguments allowed the security manager, but that's not the case anymore. I could potentially call nullSafeLoadClass directly using ServiceLoaderUtilInvoker, but it’s tricky since there's no direct public API. Tests already use the invoker for safeLoadClass and newInstance, so need to adjust methods to handle nullSafeLoadClass, while ensuring no metadata edits will cause issues.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_039c11950725165e016a246bdb8abc81968bddced91da34590\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJGvlA-v8Sfq-J4YY-rPQuVIZkT0UQxp8jII838ItRXe03ekaNSloGK9FbxDlQq532ZiVCZKAWLK8Rv8O-Cqn9GpWs21Zg4fdj4iE_BqkKYsKTkFYOJSHxzDSntThgS6h2A4XylKE5uBPXCx8j6v0dmQDQib8tB73jYwR4jJH5oyIBsRtmJ2Lf6w_WYAk0D8OfWp7G4nNF8BDm5qWx3QxsEBkq0gqHOmq6qDS98ri6TEuEDxS4CChpupLW-9Rj5YHl2MvQQZTz-CbVzBSbi1XrW-hjHb8k_MsNOdomMrDlN0kM0fRrOog40mQXReIXdAFK0ZZaVTJAiZhmrSE9QuDLg9jP9kOq9KzVHPWSrj4ANbyEaqtFrT10TwGnyW7f2mZv8IhnkJN8Djri4b2GiKkm8N0TIEVAibG94SsKWEf7bOnBIUuf3VpnnLwy-79KfKrkRm_qhf6JsLyfRNxgzyRwjfNQwZ7jehmxBg-Cz50QVKmx8OJZY8ePNgnM3RIM3SnDPdgWfQKY2kn8_dsbXp7IYUiXhYmrM2MSYkdZrDm